Main aim of java 1.8 version:
- Simplify the java programming
- Enable functional programming
- Write more readable and concise code

Java 8 Features
1) Interface changes:
    - upto java 1.7 we can write only abstract method but from the java 1.8 we can write concrete method inside it.
    - upto java 1.7 we can only write abstract method but from 1.8 we can write default and static methods

2) Functional Interfaces (@FunctionalInterface): There are some functional interfaces got released in java 1.8 version
    - Predicate
    - Consumer
    - Supplier
    - Function

3) Lambda Expression

4) Methods References and Constructor References:
    - Method reference is a shorthand syntax of lambda expression used to call an existing method directly.

5) Stream APIs: imp for interview

6) Optional Class: basically used to avoid the NullPointerException

7) Special Iterator

8) String Joiner

9) Collection Framework Changes (for each method)

10) Data and Time APIs

